"make180CO		Robin Bendall, Varian, March 1995"

"For version 5.1 software"

"Calculates the following shaped SLP pulse and stores it in your shapelib:"
"Carrier on Cb, 180 degree pulse on CO 131ppm away, null at Cab."

"The carrier should be set to 46ppm."

"The fine attenuator setting must be set in the pulse sequence during the"
" pulse."

"The pulse length parameter 'pwC7' will be created if it doesn't exist."
"The name of the shaped pulse created is 'offC7.RF'."
"In the pulse sequence code, the syntax is ...shaped_pulse(!offC7!,pwC7,...  "
"where ! means double quotes (as used at the end of this sentence)."


exists('pwC7','parameter'):$exists 
if $exists<1 then create('pwC7','pulse') endif
pwC7 = 72.5*600.0/sfrq
$steps7 = pwC7*5.0   $steps7 = 2.0*trunc($steps7/2.0) + 1.0   
pwC7 = ($steps7 + 1.0)/5.0
$rf7 = 4095.0
makesinc($steps7, $rf7)
$stps7 = ''     format($steps7,0,0):$stps7     $shape7 = 'sincs' + $stps7
$freq7 = dfrq*131.0      convolute($shape7,'offC7',pwC7,$freq7)
write('line3','The SLP pulse, offC7.RF, has been created in your shapelib')
